        "## Visualize Data\n",
        "\n",
        "### Subtask:\n",
        "Create at least one graph or chart to visualize key aspects of the processed data, such as distributions of numerical columns or counts of categorical columns. The visualization will include appropriate labels and a legend.\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "973ba6ba"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "To visualize the estimated population by species with confidence intervals, I will import `matplotlib.pyplot` and `seaborn`, calculate the error for the confidence bars from the confidence interval columns, and then create a bar plot using `seaborn.barplot`.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "b8ba0099"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "The previous code failed because the `yerr` parameter in `seaborn.barplot` received a list of pandas Series objects, which `matplotlib`'s internal `errorbar` function misinterpreted, leading to a `ValueError` regarding shape. To fix this, I will explicitly convert the `Error_Lower` and `Error_Upper` Series into a 2D NumPy array for the `yerr` parameter. Additionally, I will address the `FutureWarning` by explicitly setting `hue='Species'` and `legend=False` in the `barplot` call.\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d6983da0"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Reasoning**:\n",
        "The `ValueError` arises because `seaborn.barplot` does not correctly handle 2D `yerr` arrays for asymmetric errors when internally calling `matplotlib.pyplot.errorbar` for individual bars. To correctly display asymmetric confidence intervals, I will first plot the bars using `seaborn.barplot` without `yerr`, and then manually add the asymmetric error bars to each bar using `plt.errorbar` by iterating through the bars drawn by seaborn.\n",
        "\n"

      "source": [
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# Calculate the error for confidence intervals\n",
        "df['Error_Lower'] = df['Estimated Population'] - df['Confidence Interval (Lower)']\n",
        "df['Error_Upper'] = df['Confidence Interval (Upper)'] - df['Estimated Population']\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plotting the estimated population by species\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
        "ax = sns.barplot(x='Species', y='Estimated Population', data=df, palette='viridis', hue='Species', legend=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Manually add asymmetric error bars\n",
        "for i, species in enumerate(df['Species']):\n",
        "    lower_error = df.loc[df['Species'] == species, 'Error_Lower'].values[0]\n",
        "    upper_error = df.loc[df['Species'] == species, 'Error_Upper'].values[0]\n",
        "    # Get the x-coordinate of the bar\n",
        "    x_coord = ax.patches[i].get_x() + ax.patches[i].get_width() / 2\n",
        "    # Add error bar for this bar\n",
        "    ax.errorbar(x_coord, df.loc[df['Species'] == species, 'Estimated Population'].values[0],\n",
        "                yerr=[[lower_error], [upper_error]], fmt='none', c='black', capsize=5)\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.xlabel('Species')\n",
        "plt.ylabel('Estimated Population')\n",
        "plt.title('Estimated Population by Species in Ngorongoro Crater (2023)')\n",
        "plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
